He had left Edinburgh very early, and in coming near Auchindinny, at a lonely part ot the road, a man sprang out on him, and demanded his money. James, who was a cool hand, said, “ Weel a weel, let me get it,” and stepping back, he said to Rab, “ Speak till him, my man.” In an instant Rab was standing over him, threatening strangulation if he stirred. James pushed on, leaving Rab in charge; he looked back, and saw that every at- tempt to rise was summarily put down. As he was telling Ailie the story, up came Rab with that great swing of his.
